04/01/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The Emergency Service in Tirana ordered the evacuation Sunday (January 3rd) of citizens from all flood-affected areas in northern Albania, battered by torrential rains over the past several days.
Anyone who refuses to leave will be forced to go.
Some living close to the Drin River in Shkodra have refused to leave, despite repeated urgings.
About 100 residential buildings in the region have been flooded.
Weather forecasts predict more rain this week.
(Start, Top Channel, Telegrafi, Balkan Web - 03/01/10)
